  "_comment_hooks": "The PreToolUse hook below is the runtime half of the no-cat-head-via-bash module (the H2 re-read guard): it blocks a redundant re-read of a file already read and unmodified this session. It's guarded with a `[ -f ] || exit 0` test, so it's a safe no-op until the module is present (it ships pre_read_guard.py). The module is the Read-tool half; the prose rule is the Bash-cat half, which is why `cat`/`head`/`tail` stay in the allow list (cat-of-command-output is a legitimate exception). Disable the guard for one session with H2_REREAD_GUARD_DISABLED=1.",
  "hooks": {
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Read|Edit|Write|MultiEdit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "sh -c 'f=\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/modules/no-cat-head-via-bash/pre_read_guard.py\"; [ -f \"$f\" ] || exit 0; exec python3 \"$f\"'"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
